, {"id": 46, "seek": 21944, "start": 242.12, "end": 247.12, "text": " And in fact, that was replaced by what we call ATM.", "tokens": [51498, 400, 294, 1186, 11, 300, 390, 10772, 538, 437, 321, 818, 46455, 13, 51748], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1403996487881275, "compression_ratio": 1.5887445887445888, "no_speech_prob": 0.08498726040124893}, {"id": 47, "seek": 24712, "start": 247.12, "end": 251.8, "text": " How was one of the latest technologies that we've already had for a large number of", "tokens": [50364, 1012, 390, 472, 295, 264, 6792, 7943, 300, 321, 600, 1217, 632, 337, 257, 2416, 1230, 295, 50598], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16140441174777048, "compression_ratio": 1.6145038167938932, "no_speech_prob": 0.048518966883420944}, {"id": 48, "seek": 24712, "start": 251.8, "end": 252.8, "text": " years?", "tokens": [50598, 924, 30, 50648], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16140441174777048, "compression_ratio": 1.6145038167938932, "no_speech_prob": 0.048518966883420944}, {"id": 49, "seek": 24712, "start": 252.8, "end": 257.48, "text": " Today, we have a better technology for this, and it's called MPLS.", "tokens": [50648, 2692, 11, 321, 362, 257, 1101, 2899, 337, 341, 11, 293, 309, 311, 1219, 14146, 19198, 13, 50882], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16140441174777048, "compression_ratio": 1.6145038167938932, "no_speech_prob": 0.048518966883420944}, {"id": 50, "seek": 24712, "start": 257.48, "end": 262.96, "text": " And one of the improvements that they've made with MPLS is not only speed and quality", "tokens": [50882, 400, 472, 295, 264, 13797, 300, 436, 600, 1027, 365, 14146, 19198, 307, 406, 787, 3073, 293, 3125, 51156], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16140441174777048, "compression_ratio": 1.6145038167938932, "no_speech_prob": 0.048518966883420944}, {"id": 51, "seek": 24712, "start": 262.96, "end": 268.64, "text": " of service, but they can also offer us some built-in security, and this is what you want", "tokens": [51156, 295, 2643, 11, 457, 436, 393, 611, 2626, 505, 512, 3094, 12, 259, 3825, 11, 293, 341, 307, 437, 291, 528, 51440], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16140441174777048, "compression_ratio": 1.6145038167938932, "no_speech_prob": 0.048518966883420944}, {"id": 52, "seek": 24712, "start": 268.64, "end": 276.52, "text": " to remember, MPLS networks will use what are called forwarding tables and labeling schemes", "tokens": [51440, 281, 1604, 11, 14146, 19198, 9590, 486, 764, 437, 366, 1219, 2128, 278, 8020, 293, 40244, 26954, 51834], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16140441174777048, "compression_ratio": 1.6145038167938932, "no_speech_prob": 0.048518966883420944}, {"id": 53, "seek": 27652, "start": 276.52, "end": 283.24, "text": " to ensure that, for example, our connection that we're using across the MPLS network that", "tokens": [50364, 281, 5586, 300, 11, 337, 1365, 11, 527, 4984, 300, 321, 434, 1228, 2108, 264, 14146, 19198, 3209, 300, 50700], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13763758065044016, "compression_ratio": 1.6166666666666667, "no_speech_prob": 0.025619003921747208}, {"id": 54, "seek": 27652, "start": 283.24, "end": 285.96, "text": " belongs to a provider.", "tokens": [50700, 12953, 281, 257, 12398, 13, 50836], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13763758065044016, "compression_ratio": 1.6166666666666667, "no_speech_prob": 0.025619003921747208}, {"id": 55, "seek": 27652, "start": 285.96, "end": 293.47999999999996, "text": " Our path that our information is using across their network cannot be touched by anyone", "tokens": [50836, 2621, 3100, 300, 527, 1589, 307, 1228, 2108, 641, 3209, 2644, 312, 9828, 538, 2878, 51212], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13763758065044016, "compression_ratio": 1.6166666666666667, "no_speech_prob": 0.025619003921747208}, {"id": 56, "seek": 27652, "start": 293.47999999999996, "end": 294.47999999999996, "text": " else.", "tokens": [51212, 1646, 13, 51262], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13763758065044016, "compression_ratio": 1.6166666666666667, "no_speech_prob": 0.025619003921747208}, {"id": 57, "seek": 27652, "start": 294.47999999999996, "end": 300.14, "text": " And so the providers will guarantee that our path and the devices that are using our", "tokens": [51262, 400, 370, 264, 11330, 486, 10815, 300, 527, 3100, 293, 264, 5759, 300, 366, 1228, 527, 51545], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.13763758065044016, "compression_ratio": 1.6166666666666667, "no_speech_prob": 0.025619003921747208}, {"id": 58, "seek": 30014, "start": 300.14, "end": 307.3, "text": " path cannot be touched or used by anyone else while they're being used for our transmission.", "tokens": [50364, 3100, 2644, 312, 9828, 420, 1143, 538, 2878, 1646, 1339, 436, 434, 885, 1143, 337, 527, 11574, 13, 50722], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11452169872465588, "compression_ratio": 1.7431906614785992, "no_speech_prob": 0.47859838604927063}, {"id": 59, "seek": 30014, "start": 307.3, "end": 312.38, "text": " So they can guarantee that the path that our information is taking is ours.", "tokens": [50722, 407, 436, 393, 10815, 300, 264, 3100, 300, 527, 1589, 307, 1940, 307, 11896, 13, 50976], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11452169872465588, "compression_ratio": 1.7431906614785992, "no_speech_prob": 0.47859838604927063}, {"id": 60, "seek": 30014, "start": 312.38, "end": 316.41999999999996, "text": " And so they'll say things like, you don't need to encrypt because nobody can get to your", "tokens": [50976, 400, 370, 436, 603, 584, 721, 411, 11, 291, 500, 380, 643, 281, 17972, 662, 570, 5079, 393, 483, 281, 428, 51178], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11452169872465588, "compression_ratio": 1.7431906614785992, "no_speech_prob": 0.47859838604927063}, {"id": 61, "seek": 30014, "start": 316.41999999999996, "end": 317.82, "text": " information.", "tokens": [51178, 1589, 13, 51248], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11452169872465588, "compression_ratio": 1.7431906614785992, "no_speech_prob": 0.47859838604927063}, {"id": 62, "seek": 30014, "start": 317.82, "end": 323.14, "text": " But I know companies that are using MPLS and still encrypt the information because even", "tokens": [51248, 583, 286, 458, 3431, 300, 366, 1228, 14146, 19198, 293, 920, 17972, 662, 264, 1589, 570, 754, 51514], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11452169872465588, "compression_ratio": 1.7431906614785992, "no_speech_prob": 0.47859838604927063}, {"id": 63, "seek": 30014, "start": 323.14, "end": 328.18, "text": " though the providers will tell us that nobody can get to those paths, there is one entity", "tokens": [51514, 1673, 264, 11330, 486, 980, 505, 300, 5079, 393, 483, 281, 729, 14518, 11, 456, 307, 472, 13977, 51766], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.11452169872465588, "compression_ratio": 1.7431906614785992, "no_speech_prob": 0.47859838604927063}, {"id": 64, "seek": 32818, "start": 328.18, "end": 331.34000000000003, "text": " that can, and that is the provider themselves.", "tokens": [50364, 300, 393, 11, 293, 300, 307, 264, 12398, 2969, 13, 50522], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15264161742559754, "compression_ratio": 1.6370656370656371, "no_speech_prob": 0.032698504626750946}, {"id": 65, "seek": 32818, "start": 331.34000000000003, "end": 335.62, "text": " And just because we're paying them for a service doesn't mean that we should trust them to", "tokens": [50522, 400, 445, 570, 321, 434, 6229, 552, 337, 257, 2643, 1177, 380, 914, 300, 321, 820, 3361, 552, 281, 50736], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15264161742559754, "compression_ratio": 1.6370656370656371, "no_speech_prob": 0.032698504626750946}, {"id": 66, "seek": 32818, "start": 335.62, "end": 338.34000000000003, "text": " be able to see our information.", "tokens": [50736, 312, 1075, 281, 536, 527, 1589, 13, 50872], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15264161742559754, "compression_ratio": 1.6370656370656371, "no_speech_prob": 0.032698504626750946}, {"id": 67, "seek": 32818, "start": 338.34000000000003, "end": 345.42, "text": " And so it may be required that even though MPLS has built-in security that we would still", "tokens": [50872, 400, 370, 309, 815, 312, 4739, 300, 754, 1673, 14146, 19198, 575, 3094, 12, 259, 3825, 300, 321, 576, 920, 51226], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15264161742559754, "compression_ratio": 1.6370656370656371, "no_speech_prob": 0.032698504626750946}, {"id": 68, "seek": 32818, "start": 345.42, "end": 350.7, "text": " use authentication and encryption to protect that traffic based on its value.", "tokens": [51226, 764, 26643, 293, 29575, 281, 2371, 300, 6419, 2361, 322, 1080, 2158, 13, 51490], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15264161742559754, "compression_ratio": 1.6370656370656371, "no_speech_prob": 0.032698504626750946}, {"id": 69, "seek": 32818, "start": 350.7, "end": 356.78000000000003, "text": " Now what you want to remember about MPLS is that it uses technology that is forwarding", "tokens": [51490, 823, 437, 291, 528, 281, 1604, 466, 14146, 19198, 307, 300, 309, 4960, 2899, 300, 307, 2128, 278, 51794], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15264161742559754, "compression_ratio": 1.6370656370656371, "no_speech_prob": 0.032698504626750946}, {"id": 70, "seek": 35678, "start": 356.78, "end": 363.5, "text": " tables and labeling schemes to ensure that those paths are our paths and nobody can", "tokens": [50364, 8020, 293, 40244, 26954, 281, 5586, 300, 729, 14518, 366, 527, 14518, 293, 5079, 393, 50700], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1890453482573887, "compression_ratio": 1.4054054054054055, "no_speech_prob": 0.008256303146481514}, {"id": 71, "seek": 35678, "start": 363.5, "end": 364.7, "text": " get to them.", "tokens": [50700, 483, 281, 552, 13, 50760], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1890453482573887, "compression_ratio": 1.4054054054054055, "no_speech_prob": 0.008256303146481514}, {"id": 72, "seek": 35678, "start": 364.7, "end": 371.26, "text": " And that's the built-in security that is part of what we call MPLS networks for wide-area", "tokens": [50760, 400, 300, 311, 264, 3094, 12, 259, 3825, 300, 307, 644, 295, 437, 321, 818, 14146, 19198, 9590, 337, 4874, 12, 35425, 51088], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1890453482573887, "compression_ratio": 1.4054054054054055, "no_speech_prob": 0.008256303146481514}, {"id": 73, "seek": 35678, "start": 371.26, "end": 372.82, "text": " network capabilities.", "tokens": [51088, 3209, 10862, 13, 51166], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1890453482573887, "compression_ratio": 1.4054054054054055, "no_speech_prob": 0.008256303146481514}], "language": "en"}